{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2013}} {{Use British English|date=January 2013}} {{Refimprove|date=October 2011}} {{Infobox road |country=GBR |type=A |route=5127 |image= Lichfield Road (A5127) in Aston, Birmingham - geograph.org.uk - 996509.jpg |image_notes= The A5127, Lichfield Road in [[Aston]] |subtype=minor |length_mi= |direction_a= |terminus_a = |direction_b= |terminus_b = |junction = |destinations= }}
The '''A5127''' is a major [[road]] in [[England]] which runs between [[Birmingham]] and [[Lichfield]], [[Staffordshire]]. For much of the route the road follows the old route of the [[A38 road|A38]] which has since been moved in order to by-pass places such as [[Erdington]] and [[Sutton Coldfield]] and form a [[relief road]] from Birmingham city centre to [[Gravelly Hill Interchange|Spaghetti Junction]].
The part from the county boundary, through [[Shenstone, Staffordshire|Shenstone]] to Lichfield was one of the roads of the [[Lichfield Turnpike Trust]], established in 1729.<ref name= "LichAct">Local Act, 2 Geo. II, c.5.</ref> Beyond Lichfield, it joins the Roman [[Ryknild Street]] at [[Streethay]]<ref name= "Margary305">Margary, Ivan (1967). Roman Roads in Britain. John Baker Publishers., pp. 305-6.</ref> and immediately after that joins the present A38.
==Route== Main places and junctions<ref>coordinates from [[OpenStreetMap]]</ref> along the A5127:
* [[Birmingham]] * [[Aston]], Birmingham * A38(M) [[Aston Expressway]] Junction ({{Coord|52.49234|-1.88857|region:GB-BIR_type:landmark}}) * [[M6 motorway]] Junction 6 (Gravelly Hill Interchange / Spaghetti Junction; {{Coord|52.50941|-1.85938|region:GB-BIR_type:landmark}}) * [[Gravelly Hill]], Birmingham * [[Erdington]], Birmingham ({{Coord|52.52457|-1.84049|region:GB-BIR_type:landmark}}) * [[A452 road|A452]] Chester Road junction ({{Coord|52.53345|-1.82903|region:GB-BIR_type:landmark}}) * [[Wylde Green]], Birmingham * [[Sutton Coldfield]], Birmingham ({{Coord|52.56507|-1.82236|region:GB-BIR_type:landmark}}) * Passes near [[Sutton Park]] * [[A453 road|A435]] Tamworth Road junction ({{Coord|52.57107|-1.82308|region:GB-BIR_type:landmark}}) * [[A454 road|A434]] junction ({{Coord|52.57893|-1.82947|region:GB-BIR_type:landmark}}) * [[Four Oaks, Birmingham]] * Birmingham & West Midlands/ Staffordshire boundary ({{Coord|52.60696|-1.83815|region:GB-BIR_type:landmark}}) * [[Shenstone, Staffordshire|Shenstone]], [[Staffordshire]] * [[Wall, Staffordshire|Wall]] junction with [[M6 Toll]] ({{Coord|52.64555|-1.83432|region:GB-BIR_type:landmark}}), [[A5 road (Great Britain)|A5]] and [[A5148 road|A5148]] (leading to [[A38 road (Great Britain)|A38]]) * [[A461 road|A461]]/ [[A51 road|A51]] Junction ({{Coord|52.67609|-1.83145|region:GB_type:landmark}}) * [[Lichfield]], Staffordshire * A38 Junction ({{Coord|52.69270|-1.78813|region:GB_type:landmark}}) This route closely follows the [[Cross-City Line]].
