The '''Bowie Canyon''' is a [[submarine canyon]] located in the [[Bering Sea]].<ref name=Wolfram>{{cite web|title=What are the coordinates of Bowie Canyon|url=http://www.wolframalpha.com/entities/undersea_feature_coordinates/what_are_the_coordinates_of_bowie_canyon/i8/os/qn/|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130209093149/http://www.wolframalpha.com/entities/undersea_feature_coordinates/what_are_the_coordinates_of_bowie_canyon/i8/os/qn/|dead-url=yes|archive-date=9 February 2013|publisher=[[Wolfram Alpha]]|accessdate=30 March 2012}}</ref>   It is a submerged line of demarkation between the  [[Bowers Ridge]] and the [[Aleutian Ridge]].<ref>{{cite journal|last=Gibson|first=William|author2=Nichols, Haven|title=Configuration of the Aleutian Ridge Rat Islands — Semisopchnoi I to west of Buldir I|journal=[[Bulletin of the Geological Society of America]]|date=October 1953|volume=64|pages=1173–1188|url=https://docs.google.com/viewer?a=v&q=cache:W_Mr1SKC0l4J:gsabulletin.gsapubs.org/content/64/10/1173.full.pdf+&hl=en&gl=us&pid=bl&srcid=ADGEESi9THVzKLoc9pdmcf3HYewynEhF_ifP6t19v656juCkekrnOonChreWIk6JFN0HjPeNHXYRXg9u96VaJE1-PgKg8U69Mc7RU5eyBADQUUYgTOIuDXo4RP8HgZp-I41MGxINVpaP&sig=AHIEtbSF3tThFhYGP6Q864FD7HwUG_y9OA&pli=1|accessdate=30 March 2012}}</ref>   At its deepest point, it is 1.3 miles deep.<ref name=Wolfram/>   It is named after [[United States|American]] geodetic engineer, [[William Bowie (engineer)|William Bowie]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Undersea Features History|url=http://earth-info.nga.mil/gns/html/history.htm#B|publisher=[[National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency]]|accessdate=30 March 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211184523/http://earth-info.nga.mil/gns/html/history.htm#B|archivedate=11 February 2012|df=}}</ref>

