The '''Chios Strait''',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.geographic.org/geographic_names/name.php?uni=9108334&fid=2198&c=greece |title=Chios Strait, Greece - Geographical Names, map, geographic coordinates}}</ref> or the '''Chios Channel'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0RpinyIErCcC&pg=PA8&lpg=PA8&dq=chios+strait&source=bl&ots=9K5Ai09UdR&sig=sBKjS0R3dr34AqTVov8rmsg1UsU&hl=en&sa=X&ei=3ISJVfzsDMrr-QGaiICIBA&ved=0CFQQ6AEwDA#v=onepage&q=chios%20strait&f=false |title=Library of Congress Subject Headings - Library of Congress - Google Books}}</ref> as referred to by some sources, is a relatively narrow [[strait]] in the eastern [[Aegean Sea]] that separates the [[Greece|Greek]] island of [[Chios]] from the [[Anatolia]]n mainland and from the [[Aegean Region]] of [[Turkey]].
==Geography== [[File:Sunset at Çeşme overlooking Chios.jpg|thumb|right|Sunset over the mountains of Chios as viewed from Çeşme]] The Chios Strait is approximately 3 nautical miles<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sailingissues.com/greekislands/chios.html |title=Chios island - Chios maps for sailing holidays and yacht charters}}</ref> in width, and it is the body of water that separates Chios from the [[isthmus]]es along the western extremity of the [[Karaburun Peninsula, Turkey|Karaburun Peninsula]] in Turkey. The peninsula hosts many major districts and cities in [[İzmir Province]], including the municipality of [[Çeşme]], the westernmost city along the peninsula and, therefore, the closest to Chios. Çeşme is one of the northern cities of the [[Turkish Riviera]], and almost its entire coastline is situated along the waters of the strait. In many situations, such as in the photograph to the right, the mountains of Chios and the Chios Strait can easily be viewed from Turkey, and vice versa along the east coast of Chios from settlements such as [[Karfas]]. The hospitable water conditions of the Chios Strait make it a very common tourism and boating destination on both the Greek and Turkish coasts.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chios.com/en/about-chios |title=About Chios}}</ref>
==See also== *[[Aegean Sea]] *[[Çeşme]] *[[Chios]] *[[Gulf of İzmir]] *[[Karaburun Peninsula, Turkey|Karaburun Peninsula]] *[[Karfas]]
